ce:section.ce:para:
The experimental setup for the photo-Fenton process is shown in Fig. S1. The experimental conditions included a material loading density of 1.2 g/cm2, a 50 mg/L HA solution, and a PMS dosage of 5.0 mM. Prior to the start of the experiment, PMS was added to the HA solution and stirred well. The pH of the solution was then adjusted to 7.0 ± 0.1 using a 0.01 M NaOH solution. A 500 W iodine-tungsten lamp was used to simulate solar radiation, providing an illuminance of 1.9 kW/m2. The HA degradation experiment commenced once the cooling system and light source were activated, and it was conducted for 1 h. Samples of 5 mL were collected at 0, 15, 30, and 60 min during the degradation process to calculate the HA removal rate, mineralization rate, PMS consumption rate, apparent rate constant (k

                           obs
                        ), and degradation synergy coefficient (See Texts S2–4 for detailed calculations).
